  <p>National indicators show a slow-down in new properties construction so far this year,
    given that until July, the amounts alloted to construction works within the country have
    failed to exceed those of the same period of 2018, as collateral effect to the public
    spending budget reduction.</p>

  <p>Notwithstanding, housing institutes continue to implement new strategies in order to
    revitalize the market toward years-end, highlighting the Infonavit’s increase in credit
    limit for its lower income affiliates, thus encouraging the population to acquire new
    homes; while Fovissste, made a steady progress in its loan program scheduled for 2019,
    having served already more than 80,000 families which were in the search of new home.
    Consequently, a greater momentum in the housing industry is expected during 4Q19.</p>

